<!-- /News Item Row --><tr>
<td width="33"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=33 height=1 border="0"></td>
<td>
<a name="PQN274661"></a>
<br>
<span class="headline">Fennin Ro Rune Swap Follow-Up</span><br>
<span class="byline">3/26/01, 3:49 PST | <a href="mailto:aracnakat@rpgplanet.com">Aracnakat</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">Dynamite Shortfuze sent in this follow-up to the great Rune Faire held this weekend on Fennin Ro.

<blockquote>Despite low initial turnout, given time several people managed to show
up and get what they wanted. I guess I went a little too far in making
the event earlier, and next time I'll try to balance the meeting time
better for everyone.<br><br>
  I would like to give a HUGE thanks to Omnip Otentone, who, of her own
initiative, advertised the faire for the whole week in various zones,
and also brought over 300 runes with her to the faire. I would also like
to extend a large thank you to Tarabella Ambrosious, who also
independantly advertised to her guild and several of her friends,
brought runes which numbered second only to Omnip's, and researched
spells successfully for several younger wizards who were unable. Lastly,
a large thank you goes out to all the wizards (and our warrior guests)
who made it to the event and had fun.<br><br>
  Also, next month, there will be no mere Rune Trade. Next month, I will
be hosting Fennin Ro's first monthly Wizard Faire. We will have
contests, games, prizes, a lottery, duels, and, on top of it all, the
Rune Trade! Great fun is to be had, but obviously, I cannot do it on my
own. I already have several wizards willing to support the faire, but we
can only do better with more! I would like to encourage fully any and
all people who are interested in helping out to <a href="mailto:fenninrunes@hotmail.com">email me</a>.<br><br>



Be it with prize donations, queries, ideas (I'd REALLY like some ideas
for games and contests) or anything else. Also, I am just one brewer,
and had JUST enough Ol'Tujim's to keep everyone supplied this time, so
if anyone else would like to lend their skills to the cause, I encourage
everyone to bring some of their own stock.<br><br>

I've included a couple
pictures of us all discussing what we'd do for April. <ul><li><a href="http://www.planeteverquest.com/images/image.asp?/images/news/fr032501-1.jpg">Screenshot 1</a>
<li><a href="http://www.planeteverquest.com/images/image.asp?/images/news/fr032501-2.jpg">Screenshot 2
<li><a href="http://www.planeteverquest.com/images/image.asp?/images/news/fr032501-3.jpg">Screenshot 3</a>

</ul>

I'm looking forward to next month and hope for another great time!</blockquote></span><br><br>
</td>
<td width="10"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=10 height=1 border="0"></td>
</tr>
