<br>
<span class="headline">Fazzeal's Journal Udate</span><br>
<span class="byline">3/23/01, 12:28 PST | <a href="mailto:delrachnid@cazic-thule.com">Delrachnid</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem"><blockquote>Fazzeal has updated and some how has sent this back to our guild hall. We eagerly await word of his next update, as we all gather within our tavern to hear our bard share the adventures of Fazzeal Draconis with us.<br><br>  
 
An excerpt from his latest update:<br><br>
 
"The Guard came upon Fazzeal high up in the pass as he was preparing his camp in what the Dark Elf thought was a secluded spot. Since Fazz was preparing his camp and the stars were already coming out, the Shadow Knight didn't think that any human would be able to see well enough to detect his Teir'Dal heritage. The only warning he got was when he heard the twigs snapping and the rocks sliding as the Guard charged into camp. He offered no chance for Fazzeal to explain before he began swinging his mace and cursing him for living."<br><br>
 
We invite any interested in also sharing the experiences which trial this young shadowknight.<br><br>
 
Fazzeals Journal may be found within the scriptures of our guild hall: <a href="http://www.signofone.org">www.signofone.org</a></blockquote>
 </span><br><br>
